checkProposal(bytes32).details: Checks the outcome of a proposal, for this to be sucessful the time at which this function is called MUST be after the end Time of the voting. It is purposley not possible to check a proposal midvote.

params.proposal: A valid proposal that has been created, member function checks proposal validity

createProposal(bytes32,address[]).details: Creates a new proposal to be voted on

params.ballot_names: The list of all addresses who are being voted on
params.new_proposal: The UID of other unique identifier for proposals, it MUST be unique

decimals().details: Returns the number of decimals of the token. Note that since this is a voting token we do not want it to be divisible

getBalance(address).details: Returns the balance of voting tokens of a given address

mint(address,uint8).details: Currently this is allowing the owner to send this, however the process of this will most often change when  connected to a dao, it could even be set up automatically to disperse at a given time.

params.votes: the given amount of votes to give to a certain address

vote(bytes32,(address[],address)).details: Allows an given address to  vote on a proposal given by the proposal name, and their candidate choices Each address can only vote ONCE

params.proposal: A valid proposal that has been created, member function checks proposal validity
params.voters_choices: A structure that has the voters choices and the name of the voter
